I live close the Wrigley stadium so I walked up to McDonald's to get an early afternoon snack. I ordered at the kiosk and it was easy enough, everything was super clean and the kiosks all had their own personal sanitizer stations too. The staff were really polite too.  I wanted to try their pumpkin cream pie as well as their apple cream pie so that's what I ordered to go. Unfortunately, I was given the wrong order and I discovered this on unboxing them at home. They gave me two strawberry pies instead. I don't like strawberry pies and so I called in to let them know I've received the wrong order and would like my original order.  Shockingly enough, the staff member who picked up tried to gaslight me. She kept insinuating that I was lying by constantly repeating, "that's not possible, we're outta stock on the strawberry pies". She said it about 6 times. I know for a fact they weren't outta stock because I got not one, but TWO. I even told her that I have a picture of it as well as my bill. Anyway, she kept making it out to seem like I was deluded which I found super nasty. The kiosk mentions what's outta stock and it's impossible to order something on the menu which isn't in stock. For example - their strawberry shake and strawberry ice cream sundae was out of stock at the time I ordered. But not the strawberry pies, so I wonder why she was lying about it?  And why was it such a big deal to own up to a mistake? She could've have just apologized instead of being so mean about it. Oh well. I guess it takes all sorts to make this world.  The two stars is for the sweet staff member who opened the door for me as I walked in.
